I'll wander on with tentless heed,
line_2: Till fate shall snap the brittle thread;

line_1: I'll wander on with tentless heed,
line_2: I'll Iay me with th' inglorious dead,

line_1: Nor midst their Joy the fatal Engine heed;
line_2: The busy Flocks peck up the scatter'd Seed,

line_1: And here arriv'd, only Thy Dangers heed.
line_2: Forget th' ambitious Subject of their Speed,

line_1: Nor will thy mournful Murmurs heed.
line_2: Fly, wretched Stream, with all thy speed,

line_1: That Noble Sciences so little heed,
line_2: Their Clodpate Off-spring scarce are bred to Read.

line_1: The winter night, I take but little heed
line_2: Thou read me curious passages to speed

line_1: Return not in haste, nor of dressing take heed;
line_2: For beauty, like yours, no assistance can need.

line_1: Toil was not then. Of nothing took they Heed,
line_2: And o'er vast Plains their Herds and Flocks to feed:

line_1: Toil was not then. Of nothing took they Heed,
line_2: Blest Sons of Nature they! True Golden Age indeed!

line_1: Ever to my heart take heed;
Bade her their joyous footsteps heed,
line_2: Nor fear to sow the smallest seed.
